Following the upgrade to *JIRA 5.2.x*, the user's {{atlassian-jira.log}} are cluttered with messages like the following:
{code}
2013-03-13 19:45:06,112 http-bio-21443-exec-3 INFO grd8st 1134x2399x1 vyz2ff 10.3.34.33 /browse/TEST-1 [atlassian.jira.security.WorkflowBasedPermissionManager]      attach not granted by workflow perm granting attach to Single User ''
2013-03-13 19:45:06,114 http-bio-21443-exec-3 INFO grd8st 1134x2399x1 vyz2ff 10.3.34.33 /browse/TEST-1 [atlassian.jira.security.WorkflowBasedPermissionManager] attach granted by permission scheme and workflow perm granting attach to Group 'p2_changetool'
{code}

They will be displayed when an issue is viewed when using workflow step specific permissions. The workaround is to disable it from the {{log4j.properties}} as per the following from the original:
{code}
log4j.logger.com.atlassian.jira.security = INFO, console, filelog
log4j.additivity.com.atlassian.jira.security = false
{code}

to something like:

{code}
log4j.logger.com.atlassian.jira.security = WARN, console, filelog
log4j.additivity.com.atlassian.jira.security = false
{code}

However, it would fit better in it's own log file in order not to clutter the standard log file {{atlassian-jira.log}}. Maybe something like {{atlassian-jira-workflow.log}} would be an option.

