https://jira.atlassian.com/secure/Dashboard.jspa doesn't include the Atlassian Connector for Eclipse in the project list.

Step to reproduce the issue: 
# change the attachment path in the database: 
{code}
update propertystring set propertyvalue='/Users/yilinmo/work/reprod/jira/home/atlassian-jira-5.2-standalone/import/attachments' where id = (select id from propertyentry where property_key = 'jira.path.attachments');
{code}
which set the attachment path to the import attachment folder.
# disable the option using the default attachment folder path:
{code}
update propertynumber set propertyvalue =0 where id= (select id from propertyentry where property_key = 'jira.path.attachments.use.default.directory');
{code}
# Restart JIRA then import a project from the XML backup.
# When clicking the next button it will return to the same page without any error. 

The root cause of the issue is that in the project import, we've got a canonical path check between the attachment folder and the import attachment folder, but the error message for this issue is not showing in the log or UI. 

This is can happen for the user which upgrade from an older version of JIRA which allow to customized the attachment folder.

