In an Atlassian gadget, when receiving a REST call response with status 500, the following code message is shown in a red box: "An internal server error occurred when requesting resource .". This should be "An internal server error occurred when requesting resource http://localhost/jira/rest/someService/someAction."

The url is not shown due to a bug in the ajs.gadget.base.js file, in the handle500 function.

As it is right now:
handle500: function (evt, data, settings){ 
var msg = AJS.format(gadget.getMsg("gadget.common.error.500", settings.url, settings.url)); AG.sysMsg.addError(msg);
}

There is a bracket placed incorrectly, the method should be (as in handle404):
handle500: function (evt, data, settings){ 
var msg = AJS.format(gadget.getMsg("gadget.common.error.500"), settings.url, settings.url); AG.sysMsg.addError(msg); 
}

